    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think this is a reasonable common adjustment to an EWM in practice, but not sure it should be a default, as it's not really the \"standard\" definition, e.g. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moving_average#Exponential_moving_average\r\n\r\nSo I could see expanding the api here, or this is not that hard to do yourself.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nseed_ewm = df['B'].rolling(2).mean().iloc[1]\r\n\r\ndf.iloc[:2] = seed_ewm\r\n\r\ndf.ewm(span=2,min_periods=2,adjust=False).mean()\r\nOut[129]: \r\n            B\r\n0         NaN\r\n1   10.500000\r\n2  270.166667\r\n3   90.722222\r\n4   30.907407\r\n5   10.969136\r\n\r\n10.5 * (1 - 2/3) + 400 * (2/3)\r\nOut[130]: 270.16666666666663\r\n```"
  },
